public void visitBit(java.lang.Byte[] instances)
Description copied from interface: DomainVisitor
Gets called if the subtree is a single bit. The Byte[] contains the diffent instances that was passed to acceptDomainVisitor method. This will happen if you have a B in your domain without a ^ specifier.
